verbs.description: overneutralize (third-person singular simple present overneutralizes, present participle overneutralizing, simple past and past participle overneutralized)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make more neutral than required or expected, or (chemistry) beyond the neutral pH value.
examples: If you will overneutralize the colors in the background and increase the Chroma of the colors in the foreground, you will discover that depth will begin to come into your picture.
